HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 103
BY REPRESENTATIVES WALTERS AND MARCELLE
A RESOLUTION
To designate Wednesday, April 8, 2026, as Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated, Day
at the state capitol.
WHEREAS, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated, was founded on January 13,
1913, by twenty-two collegiate women at Howard University who sought to use their
collective strength to promote academic excellence, provide scholarships and support to
those in need, educate and stimulate participation in the establishment of positive public
policy, and address issues affecting their communities; and
WHEREAS, since its founding, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated, has been
committed to civic engagement and public service, including historic efforts to promote
voter education, civil rights, and participation in the democratic process, while encouraging
leadership and advocacy in communities across the nation; and
WHEREAS, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated, was incorporated in 1930 and
is a private, nonprofit organization that provides assistance and support through established
programs in local communities and throughout the world; and
WHEREAS, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated, is the largest African
American Greek-letter sorority, a sisterhood of more than three hundred fifty thousand
predominantly African American college-educated women, comprised of more than one
thousand fifty chapters worldwide; and
WHEREAS, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated, maintains a strong presence
throughout the state of Louisiana, with numerous alumnae and collegiate chapters actively
serving their communities through programs focused on education, health, economic
empowerment, and civic engagement; and
