WHEREAS, the members of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated, stand on the
shoulders of giants whose leadership has left an enduring imprint on the history of this state;
these members include former state representatives Renee Gill Pratt, Rosalind Peychaud,
Jalila Jefferson Bullock, and the late Pinkie Carolyn Wilkerson; former state senators Diana
E. Bajoie, Karen Carter Peterson, and Cheryl Gray Evans; and Louisiana Senate Secretary
Yolanda J. Dixon; and
WHEREAS, to uplift, encourage, and develop the global community, Delta Sigma
Theta Sorority, Incorporated, focuses its efforts on the Five-Point Programmatic Thrust of
economic development, educational development, international awareness and involvement,
physical and mental health, and political awareness and involvement; and
WHEREAS, the organizational structure and governance of Delta Sigma Theta
Sorority, Incorporated, are vested in the Grand Chapter, which meets at a biennial national
convention and regional conferences held in the organization's seven geographic regions
during nonconvention years; and
WHEREAS, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated, emphasizes its commitment
to community service and academic achievement, as well as its quest for excellence in all
endeavors, through the success of its public service programs; its members are truly
deserving of the highest recognition for their outstanding contributions to Louisiana and
beyond.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby designate Wednesday, April 8, 2026, as Delta Sigma
Theta Sorority, Incorporated, Day at the state capitol; does hereby commend and recognize
the women of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated, for their exceptional achievements
and manifold contributions; and does hereby extend enduring appreciation to the
organization and its members for the tremendous pride and honor they bring to their local
communities, the state of Louisiana, and the United States of America.
